  "1998 APMO Problems/Problem 2": {
    "parse": {
      "title": "1998 APMO Problems/Problem 2",
      "pageid": 21710,
      "revid": 158892,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Problem\">Problem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_APMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Problem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Show that for any positive integers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/7/d/c7d457e388298246adb06c587bccd419ea67f7e8.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"11\" height=\"10\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/1/3/8136a7ef6a03334a7246df9097e5bcc31ba33fd2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"10\" height=\"14\" />, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/8/2/482ac7d81b9c725b4aabb4eb5c63f3844102913f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(36a + b)(36b + a)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"146\" height=\"20\" /> cannot be a power of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/1/c/41c544263a265ff15498ee45f7392c5f86c6d151.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2$\" width=\"8\" height=\"12\" />.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution_1\">Solution 1</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_APMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Solution 1\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>First, assume that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/8/2/482ac7d81b9c725b4aabb4eb5c63f3844102913f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(36a + b)(36b + a)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"146\" height=\"20\" /> is a power of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/1/c/41c544263a265ff15498ee45f7392c5f86c6d151.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2$\" width=\"8\" height=\"12\" />. \nLet <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/7/b/67b0bce8b0552d10301badeb20e9acee794cd977.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$36a + b = 2^m = p$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"139\" height=\"18\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/8/c/48cbdc9210dc454657257b29166a5eb65be4d19e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$36b + a = 2^n = q$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"135\" height=\"18\" />.\nThen <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/0/c/20cd65a65ac85a9bd191c9ab814f0c3df58a4ce2.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\frac{1}{36} &lt; \\frac{p}{q} = \\frac{2^m}{2^n} = 2^{m-n} &lt; 36\\]\" width=\"214\" height=\"40\" />\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/1/6/31624db3ca6204c7259ecf67a212ab41aba473a4.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[-6 &lt; m - n &lt; 6\\]\" width=\"128\" height=\"13\" />\n</p><p>Consider <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/6/2/b62dc4f8f7baade51297e136a3b379cadecd1110.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$4^m - 4^n = p^2 - q^2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"143\" height=\"20\" />. Factoring out <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/c/7/6c78734258d2d82aeb28c1631e8f1798154c888d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$4^n$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"17\" height=\"13\" /> gives \n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/4/d/84d36b8fe2bb8d0f046071d15a09eba22cb01f6b.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[4^n(4^{m-n}-1) = p^2 - q^2 = 1295(a^2 - b^2)\\]\" width=\"310\" height=\"20\" />\n</p><p>Because <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/b/0/eb0d37dbbaac4799a4f549bf724f067ea9fd9930.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$1295(a^2 - b^2)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"107\" height=\"21\" /> contains odd factors and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/4/7/c4787aed3f28e29033eaaf335c6c838355fa6015.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$1295$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"35\" height=\"13\" /> divides <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/8/9/78916550838bd31d66e4cdefbc366edb11fd00bd.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$37$\" width=\"18\" height=\"12\" />, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/e/2/7e20d2a697682c28bf24300be063897764669245.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$4^{m-n}-1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"73\" height=\"18\" /> must also divide <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/8/9/78916550838bd31d66e4cdefbc366edb11fd00bd.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$37$\" width=\"18\" height=\"12\" />, so \n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/6/d/06da6319f01ed06c5d27b9877b3495922c0aee9b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$4^{m-n} \\equiv  1\\mod 37$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"147\" height=\"17\" />.\n</p><p><br />\nTesting values shows that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/e/c/eec521c60534fed80cc321be32e7347f785c145d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m-n$\" width=\"48\" height=\"8\" /> divides 18. It can be easily shown that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/1/c/51c59f59aff874589d279fe99464a8170ff40651.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m-n \\neq 0$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"82\" height=\"17\" />, so the least possible value of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/e/c/eec521c60534fed80cc321be32e7347f785c145d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m-n$\" width=\"48\" height=\"8\" /> is 18. But since <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/7/b/f7bf4bb62e0d0ebfedfcac77b69fe7e867970e7f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$-6 &lt; m - n &lt; 6$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"132\" height=\"15\" />, we reach a contradiction.\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution_2\">Solution 2</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_APMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Solution 2\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Assume that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/8/2/482ac7d81b9c725b4aabb4eb5c63f3844102913f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(36a + b)(36b + a)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"146\" height=\"20\" /> is a power of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/1/c/41c544263a265ff15498ee45f7392c5f86c6d151.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2$\" width=\"8\" height=\"12\" />. Then <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/8/b/98b7e4c455672c30d743cce7506408a40cb68129.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(m, n)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"47\" height=\"18\" /> must also be a solution to <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/9/c/49c574fbb7e499283fe5ecb74566dd3815a61ad6.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(36a + b)(36b + a) = 2^x$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"187\" height=\"20\" /> for some positive integer <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/6/e/26eeb5258ca5099acf8fe96b2a1049c48c89a5e6.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"12\" height=\"10\" />. WLOG, assume <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/b/2/9b2142770fa24b44536073e58e97ca948a989965.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m &lt; n$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"50\" height=\"10\" /> and let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/5/0/f5047d1e0cbb50ec208923a22cd517c55100fa7b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m$\" width=\"15\" height=\"8\" /> be minimal. Then the least possible value of <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/f/e/cfe19d08896a8b596644e45a027cdf92ffa495d7.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(36m + n)(36n + m)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"165\" height=\"20\" /> is <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/c/1/fc1e72d6da59a3ff54bfd7310e89ab8d2d90db14.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(37)(37) &gt; (2^5)(2^5)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"152\" height=\"21\" />. For all positive integers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/7/6/3767f0665ea4d5f0e9c58452fc5782b42a8a65a2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$x &gt; 1$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"42\" height=\"12\" />, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/0/4/b04393a3b0f3ed94ea70cc624d0afefe9f279e34.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$2^x \\equiv 0\\mod 4$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"115\" height=\"14\" />. So both <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/f/e/cfe19d08896a8b596644e45a027cdf92ffa495d7.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(36m + n)(36n + m)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"165\" height=\"20\" /> must divide 4 as well. Then <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/3/6/836c4f7d7eb7f54dad8d33af67292bf4eb81602b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(\\frac{m}{2}, \\frac{n}{2})$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"59\" height=\"34\" /> must also be a solution. But <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/5/0/f5047d1e0cbb50ec208923a22cd517c55100fa7b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m$\" width=\"15\" height=\"8\" /> is minimal and we find a smaller integer solution (because <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/5/0/f5047d1e0cbb50ec208923a22cd517c55100fa7b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$m$\" width=\"15\" height=\"8\" /> divides 4), so we reach a contradiction.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907065021\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.018 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.018 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 262/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 776/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 6618/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:21710-0!canonical and timestamp 20240907065021 and revision id 158892\n -->\n"
